[{'text': '[Narrator] Weather forecasters use them to create the nightly weather report. ', 'start': 0.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'Airline pilots use them to learn how to fly planes. Experts use them in virtually every', 'start': 6.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'industry and discipline. They are computer models. At NASA, ', 'start': 12.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'scientists use computer models to enhance their understanding of the earth, the solar system', 'start': 18.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'and the universe. NASA satellites orbiting the earth', 'start': 24.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'relay immense amounts of data to scientists on the ground, who then enter that data', 'start': 30.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'into computer model simulations. [Cynthia Rosenzweig] We have then, equations and then', 'start': 36.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'computer code which solves those equations on a day-to-day basis.', 'start': 42.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': '[Narrator] NASA is the source for most of the research satellite observations of the atmosphere,', 'start': 48.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'land and oceans. [Phil Webster] So the NASA scientists will look at the observational data and', 'start': 54.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'make theoretical projections about what a model might look like and they will build a numerical model', 'start': 60.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'based on the data and then run that on our computers and compare that to reality.', 'start': 66.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': '[Narrator] With rapid increases in computer technology, models are becoming ', 'start': 72.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'evermore powerful and sophisticated, allowing us to simulate our complex environment in greater detail.', 'start': 78.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'NASA uses a variety of weather models such as the Goddard Earth Observing System model.', 'start': 84.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'It creates an extraordinarily high resolution, realistic-looking ', 'start': 90.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': "image of our atmosphere. These GEOS-5 simulations showcase the model's ", 'start': 96.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'ability to capture fine-scale cloud features worldwide, like the swirling clouds in the Atlantic', 'start': 102.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'Ocean off the coast of North America. ', 'start': 108.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'The goal of weather models is to give the most accurate prediction of weather in the next week to ten days.', 'start': 114.0, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'In 2005, when Hurricane Katrina formed over the Atlantic Ocean, scientists', 'start': 120.0, 'duration': 5.99}, {'text': 'wanted to understand the storm. How intense was it, what was its size and structure and what ', 'start': 126.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'would be its final path? NASA satellites continuously monitored many aspects of the storm', 'start': 132.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': "from windspeed, rainfall and sea surface temperature to the storm's three-dimensional structure.", 'start': 138.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'To get a more complete picture of the storm and predict its evolution, scientists entered', 'start': 144.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'the data into a computer model. Then, high-powered supercomputers capable of trillions of calculations', 'start': 150.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'per second crunched the numbers. This process is called data assimilation.', 'start': 156.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'Data assimilation is a two-step cycle that repeats itself whenever new data becomes available. ', 'start': 162.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'In the first step, the model runs forward in time to provide an estimate of the atmosphere. In the second', 'start': 168.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'step, this estimate gets corrected using observations. The cycle begins again, each step', 'start': 174.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'building upon the last and accumulating the information from satellite and ground observations.', 'start': 180.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'Weather models are updated every six hours to include the most current observations for the next forecast.', 'start': 186.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'This approach prevents the model from straying too far from reality and acts as a checks-and-balance system', 'start': 192.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'to acheive the most accurate forecast. While weather models predict', 'start': 198.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'conditions for up to ten days, climate models predict trends over much longer periods of time.', 'start': 204.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': '[Phil Webster] The climate models that are run at the NCCS are numerical expressions of the', 'start': 210.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'various processes that make up climate. This includes things like land surface, ', 'start': 216.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'water in the ocean and the movement of air in the atmosphere. [Narrator] Just as in weather prediction, ', 'start': 222.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'data assimilation is a way of bringing all the observations of the earth together to provide an analysis of our climate', 'start': 228.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': '. One example of this technique is MERRA - the Modern Era Retrospective Analaysis for Research', 'start': 234.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'and Applications. MERRA incorporates data from the entire satellite record.', 'start': 240.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'Over 30 years of data. Its results are a data encyclopedia that can be used for research and', 'start': 246.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'analysis. MERRA can help meteorologists understand the variations associated with specific ', 'start': 252.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'weather events in the past. While MERRA gives us a climate picture across decades, the Goddard Institutde', 'start': 258.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'for Space Studies, or GISS, can extend that view across centuries. GISS models ', 'start': 264.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'have already unraveled average temperature trends over 200 years. New GISS simulations will cover the last', 'start': 270.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': "1,000 years to verify model accuracy. They'll also look forward, projecting climate", 'start': 276.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'trends to the end of the 21st century. With each satellite launched, we gain billions of measurements', 'start': 282.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'that tell us more about our planet. Having so much more data will require increases in', 'start': 288.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'computing power to synthesize this information into meaningful representations of the climate system as a whole.', 'start': 294.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': '[Phil Webster] At Goddard Space Flight Center, we have a tremendous amount of observational data,', 'start': 300.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'captured by our satellites. We have probably the largest collection of earth scientists', 'start': 306.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'in the world. And we have this new state-of-the-art computing center. So the combination of', 'start': 312.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'the scientists, data and computing puts us in a unique position to enable', 'start': 318.01, 'duration': 5.98}, {'text': 'advances in weather and climate research.', 'start': 324.01, 'duration': 17.97}]

[{'text': 'In the mid to late 70s and early 80s,
there was no game company more well known', 'start': 0.65, 'duration': 26.799}, {'text': 'than Atari.', 'start': 27.449, 'duration': 1.34}, {'text': 'With classic titles that many people still
love today, the company had it made.', 'start': 28.789, 'duration': 3.551}, {'text': 'That was of course, until their 2600 became
saturated with low quality games and the market', 'start': 32.34, 'duration': 4.88}, {'text': 'crashed.', 'start': 37.22, 'duration': 2.53}, {'text': 'In the present day, ask some younger kids
about Atari and see what they know.', 'start': 39.75, 'duration': 3.73}, {'text': 'You might be surprised.', 'start': 43.48, 'duration': 1.5}, {'text': 'But we arent here to talk about that today.', 'start': 44.98, 'duration': 1.49}, {'text': 'Were looking back at some of the best Atari
arcade games, re-released on the Game Boy', 'start': 46.47, 'duration': 3.63}, {'text': 'Advance in 2002.', 'start': 50.1, 'duration': 1.41}, {'text': 'This is Atari Anniversary Advance.', 'start': 51.51, 'duration': 8.47}, {'text': 'Atari Anniversary Advance consists of some
of the most popular Atari arcade games, like', 'start': 59.98, 'duration': 4.2}, {'text': 'Asteroids, Tempest, Super Breakout, Missile
Command, Centipede and Battlezones.', 'start': 64.18, 'duration': 4.76}, {'text': 'These games appear to have virtually no change
in bringing them to the Game Boy Advance,', 'start': 68.94, 'duration': 3.29}, {'text': 'and thats a very good thing.', 'start': 72.23, 'duration': 1.43}, {'text': 'They still very much have that old-school
arcade feel, even though you are playing it', 'start': 73.66, 'duration': 2.991}, {'text': 'on a much smaller screen.', 'start': 76.651, 'duration': 1.739}, {'text': 'Since high scores can also be saved on the
game-pak, it might be fun to lend this out', 'start': 78.39, 'duration': 3.22}, {'text': 'to some friends and see who can beat you.', 'start': 81.61, 'duration': 2.19}, {'text': 'Now, like I said, the games on this are just
like the arcade games, but controlling some', 'start': 83.8, 'duration': 3.5}, {'text': 'of them can be a bit of a pain when using
the d-pad.', 'start': 87.3, 'duration': 3.01}, {'text': 'It just feels a little bit strange, especially
in games like Asteroids where momentum picks', 'start': 90.31, 'duration': 3.8}, {'text': 'up, and this is even harder if youre using
the Game Boy Player for a bigger screen like', 'start': 94.11, 'duration': 3.799}, {'text': 'I was, since it gives you a very small delay.', 'start': 97.909, 'duration': 2.771}, {'text': 'This issue isnt present on every game,
though.', 'start': 100.68, 'duration': 2.18}, {'text': 'Tempest, Centipede and BattleZones probably
made the best transition to this control set-up,', 'start': 102.86, 'duration': 4.42}, {'text': 'while the worst for it by far is Super Breakout.', 'start': 107.28, 'duration': 1.82}, {'text': 'The game is almost impossible to control with
either the d-pad or the GameCube analog stick,', 'start': 109.1, 'duration': 4.65}, {'text': 'and its really a shame considering how
well liked it is.', 'start': 113.75, 'duration': 3.17}, {'text': 'Missile Command is actually really well suited
for the GBA controls as well, with different', 'start': 116.92, 'duration': 3.449}, {'text': 'guns being assigned to the L, R, A and B buttons.', 'start': 120.369, 'duration': 7.78}, {'text': 'Atari Anniversary Advance doesnt feature
any type of Pong like past versions of the', 'start': 128.149, 'duration': 3.781}, {'text': 'game had, but it does have an Atari Trivia
game that will make you feel like you dont', 'start': 131.93, 'duration': 3.389}, {'text': 'know anything about Atari.', 'start': 135.319, 'duration': 1.361}, {'text': 'I consider myself to be pretty knowledgeable
about gaming, but I know a lot more about', 'start': 136.68, 'duration': 3.83}, {'text': 'the period from 85 and up.', 'start': 140.51, 'duration': 1.66}, {'text': 'Apparently though, people at Atari thought
red plastic wrap would work in a video game.', 'start': 142.17, 'duration': 3.569}, {'text': 'I guess it did.', 'start': 145.739, 'duration': 1.161}, {'text': 'Im kind of surprised that there werent
more games put onto this, however.', 'start': 146.9, 'duration': 3.539}, {'text': 'Yeah, most of the best arcade games are included,
but it wouldve been nice for some old 2600', 'start': 150.439, 'duration': 4.241}, {'text': 'games as well with the amount of info the
GBA carts can hold.', 'start': 154.68, 'duration': 3.44}, {'text': 'Just dont put that port of Pac-man on it.', 'start': 158.12, 'duration': 2.3}, {'text': 'Ever.', 'start': 160.42, 'duration': 1.0}, {'text': 'As this is mostly a game for fans of the originals,
youll obviously be pleased with its aesthetics.', 'start': 161.42, 'duration': 5.209}, {'text': 'Everything has that old, classic feel that
looks awesome, especially on games like Tempest', 'start': 166.629, 'duration': 3.7}, {'text': 'and BattleZones.', 'start': 170.329, 'duration': 1.201}, {'text': 'Sound effects are also excellent, even if
they are slightly primitive.', 'start': 171.53, 'duration': 3.289}, {'text': 'Firing in Centipede is sure to put a big smile
on your face.', 'start': 174.819, 'duration': 4.2}, {'text': 'While I cant recommend this game to anyone
who really doesnt care for games from this', 'start': 179.019, 'duration': 7.661}, {'text': 'time period, as it wont change their mind,
Atari Anniversary Advance is a fantastic collection', 'start': 186.68, 'duration': 4.69}, {'text': 'of arcade titles that is sure to satisfy your
old-school appetite.', 'start': 191.37, 'duration': 2.599}, {'text': 'Just dont get too upset when your friend
beats your high score.', 'start': 193.969, 'duration': 7.181}]
